SVNet Meeting - Wednesday, December 8, 1993
 
Low Cost and Public Domain UNIX-like Operating Systems, the Great Debate
 
What:  A panel of experts will discuss comparative features of several
       low cost or PD UNIX-like operating systems at SVNet's monthly meeting.
       Panel members will discuss what each of the systems currently support,
       speculate about future directions, and answer questions from the
       audience.
 
Who:   Brad Grantham - MacBSD (NetBSD for the Mac)
       Steve Ness - Coherent
       Adam Richter - Linux
       Chris Demetrion - NetBSD
 
When:  7:30pm Wednesday, December 8, 1993
 
Where:  Sun Microsystems Bldg 6, 2750 Coast Ave, Mtn View
        Coast Ave is off of Garcia Avenue, between San Antonio and
        Amphitheatre Pkwy on the Bay side of 101 in Mountain View.
        Coast Ave looks like a private driveway that runs behind 
        Bldgs 1 and 5 on Garcia, so don't get confused.
 
        For more information, please call Paul Fronberg at (408) 246-1132
        or Ralph Barker at (408) 559-6202
 
  SVNet programs are FREE and open to the public.  Pre-registration or
  reservations are NOT required to attend the meeting.
 
  SVNet is a regional UNIX(r) and open systems users group supported by member 
  dues and contributions.  UNIX is a registered trademark of UNIX System 
  Laboratories, to which SVNet is not affiliated.
 

