From: jan@pandonia.canberra.edu.au (Jan Newmarch)
Subject: Re: Help with Mpeg_play.wdgt (need PrimitiveP.h)
Date:  6 Dec 93 07:06:49 GMT

In <1993Dec2.011306.27290@iitmax.iit.edu> grzyrob@elof.acc.iit.edu (Rob Grzywinski) writes:

>I want rtying to compile the widget version of Mpeg_play and it could
>not find the file PrimitiveP.h.  It's not in any of the dirs.  Could
>anyone direct me to the file or a way around it.

This a Motif header file for the Motif version of the widget. I have not
been able to determinbe whether or not this file can be distributed
freely. Anyway, it still requires the Motif libraries. If you don't have
these then try commenting out the -DIS_MOTIF_WIDGET in the Makefile.
This should build a widget subclassed from Core.

                        Jan
