From: dwex@aib.com (David E. Wexelblat)
Subject: Re: Xconfig
Date: Mon, 6 Dec 1993 15:17:40 GMT

In article <1993Dec6.045059.17643@news.qut.edu.au> B.Lynam@qut.edu.au writes:
>
>
>
>The only thing "wrong" with modeDB.txt, IMHO is that the monitor 
>timing should have the sync rates in it so that new modes can be 
>generated for different resolutions.

Come on, this requires exactly TWO calculations:

        Hsync = (dot-clock in Hz) / (Htotal)
        Vrefresh = (Hsync in Hz) / (Vtotal)

Where Htotal and Vtotal are the 4th numbers from the horizontal and
vertical groups, respectively.

